<section xml:id="course-expectations">
  <title>Course Expectations</title>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Save Your Spot</title>
    <p>
      Stay enrolled in this and your other courses this term by attending class and participating in required course activities during the first week of the term. Instructors have the option to disenroll a student from a class if the student has missed at least one scheduled class in person or via Zoom or required online course activity for online courses (check your syllabus for information) during the first 4 days of the week in which the course is scheduled to meet for the first time. This allows students who are on the course waitlist to be added to the course.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Course Workload and Time Management</title>
    <p>
      A standard time managment guidline is that you should expect to spend 2-3 hours outside of class studying for each hour of class time.  For this 4-hour class, that means you should spend 8-12 hours per week studying outside of class. 
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

